from dataclasses import dataclass

@dataclass
class Triple:
    subject: str
    predicate: str
    object: str

# EVOLVE-BLOCK-START

def predict(triples: list[Triple]) -> str:
        sentence = ""
        subject = None
        related_info = []

        for triple in triples:
            if subject is None:
                subject = triple.subject
                related_info.append(triple)
            elif triple.subject == subject:
                related_info.append(triple)
            else:
                # Handle a new subject - create a sentence from related_info first
                sentence += build_sentence(subject, related_info) + " "
                subject = triple.subject
                related_info = [triple]

        # Build sentence for the last subject
        if subject:
            sentence += build_sentence(subject, related_info)

        return sentence

    def build_sentence(subject, related_info):
        sentence_parts = []
        for i, triple in enumerate(related_info):
            if triple.predicate == "architecturalStyle":
                sentence_parts.append(f"{subject} is built in {triple.object} style")
            elif triple.predicate == "buildingStartDate":
                sentence_parts.append(f"Construction of {subject} started in {triple.object}")
            elif triple.predicate == "completionDate":
                sentence_parts.append(f"{subject} was completed in {triple.object}")
            elif triple.predicate == "floorCount":
                sentence_parts.append(f"{subject} has {triple.object} floors")
            elif triple.predicate == "location":
                sentence_parts.append(f"{subject} is located in {triple.object}")
            elif triple.predicate == "country":
                sentence_parts.append(f"{subject} is located in {triple.object}")
            elif triple.predicate == "isPartOf":
                sentence_parts.append(f"{subject} is part of {triple.object}")
            else:
                sentence_parts.append(f"{subject} {triple.predicate} {triple.object}")

        if len(sentence_parts) > 1:
            # Connect clauses with "which" or "where"
            final_sentence = sentence_parts[0]
            for part in sentence_parts[1:]:
                final_sentence += ", which " + part if "located" in part or "part" in part else ", and " + part
            final_sentence += "."
        else:
            final_sentence = " ".join(sentence_parts) + "."

        return final_sentence
